    "body": "Hey, looks like you're trying to compile an ERC20 directly. In 5.0 it was changed to be an abstract contract, you just need to instantiate it:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.20;\r\n\r\nimport \"[@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/v5.0.0/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol)\";\r\n\r\ncontract MyToken is ERC20 {\r\n    constructor() ERC20(\"MyToken\", \"MTK\") {}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow deploy `MyToken` instead of `ERC20` directly.\r\nClosing since it's not an issue. Feel free to submit support questions in our [community forum](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/)\r\n\r\nAlso, consider taking a look a our [Contracts Wizard](https://wizard.openzeppelin.com/)",
